<h1>URL Shortener Microservice</h1>
<div class="inside-box">
  <h2>User stories:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>I can pass a URL as a parameter and I will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response.</li>
    <li>When I visit that shortened URL, it will redirect me to my original link.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="inside-box">
  <h2>Example creation usage:</h2>
  <div class="code">
    <a href="https://mww-shorten-url.herokuapp.com/<%= links[0].url %>"><code>https://mww-shorten-url.herokuapp.com/<%= links[0].url %></a></code>
    <br>
    <a href="https://mww-shorten-url.herokuapp.com/<%= links[1].url %>"><code>https://mww-shorten-url.herokuapp.com/<%= links[1].url %></code></a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="inside-box">
  <h2>Example creation output:</h2>
  <div class="code">
    <code>{<br> <span class="indent">"original_url":"<%= links[0].url %>"</span>, <br> <span class="indent">"short_url":"<%= links[0].shortLink %>"</span> <br>}</code>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="inside-box">
  <h2>Usage:</h2>
  <div class="code">
    <a href="<%= links[0].shortLink %>"><code><%= links[0].shortLink %></code></a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="inside-box">
  <h2>Will redirect to:</h2>
  <div class="code">
    <a href="<%= links[0].url %>"><code><%= links[0].url %></code></a>
  </div>
</div>
